@Node "Project menu"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} About...
   Brings up a requester that tells about me and the program.
   The Luffar window will sleep when the About window is open.
   No action can be done until the About window is gone.

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Quit
   Shortcut: <Right Amiga> Q
   Quits the program without asking.
   You can also use the close gadget in the upper left
   corner of the @{" Luffar window " Link "Luffar Window" }.

@EndNode



@Node "Settings menu"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Auto restart
   Shortcut: <Right Amiga> R. Default checked.
   Toggles the auto restart option.
   If checked you can restart the game by clicking in the @{" board " Link "Board" }
   when the game is over.
   The computer player isn't affected other than in one player
   mode when the computer player will toggle to play the other
   symbols. Just try it and you will understand (@{" Martin Rebas " Link "Martin Rebas" } didn't).

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Russian opening
   Shortcut: <Right Amiga> O. Default checked.
   If checked the computer will play with russian opening.
   You may still play with or without russian opening.
   Russian opening is a rule to decrease the benefit of beginning.
   It means that the second cross must have two boxes
   between itself and the first cross in the middle.
   If you don't understand this, just observe the computer playing.

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Only win on five
   Shortcut: <Right Amiga> F. Default checked.
   If checked only five in a row will be counted as a winning row.
   Six in a row will be ignored.
   Luffar will restart the game when selected to avoid forbidden
   states.

   The defaults can be changed with @{" Luffar ToolTypes " Link "Luffar ToolTypes" }.

   See also the @{" rules of noughts and crosses " Link "The game of noughts and crosses" }.

@EndNode




