@Node "Restart button"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Restart button
   Rewinds to the beginning but remembers the moves done so
   you can use the @{" Ahead button " Link "Ahead button" } to step through the game.
   It will also turn off the computer players.
   See also autorestart in the @{" settings menu " Link "Settings menu" }.

@EndNode

@Node "Rewind button"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Rewind button ( << )
   Will rewind one move if possible.
   Good to use when you get angry because the computer beats you. :-)

@EndNode

@Node "Ahead button"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Ahead button ( >> )
   Will wind ahead one move if possible.
   Can be used after a restart.
   If anyone set a new move the ahead button will be ghosted.

@EndNode

@Node "Play crosses button"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Play crosses button
   Select this to make the computer play crosses.

@EndNode

@Node "Play rings button"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Play rings button
   Select this to make the computer play rings.

@EndNode

@Node "Level cycle button"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Level cycle button
   When you press this you will cycle the level.
   The level is how good the computer plays. It will think
   longer at the higher levels.

@EndNode

@Node "Style cycle button"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} Style cycle button
   If you press this button you will toggle how offensively the
   computer plays.

@EndNode

@Node "Board"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} The board contains 15x15 boxes. The symbols are put in the boxes.
   The board is also the place you press to use the autorestart option
   in the @{" settings menu " Link "Settings menu" }.

@EndNode



