@EndNode


@Node "LEVEL"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} LEVEL

   Syntax:  LEVEL=HALF_BLIND | DUMB | BAD | GOOD | JOLLY_GOOD
   Default: LEVEL=GOOD

   Set the default on the @{" level button " Link "Level cycle button" } gadget.
@EndNode


@Node "STYLE"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} STYLE

   Syntax:  STYLE=OFFENSIVE | DEFENSIVE
   Default: STYLE=OFFENSIVE

   Set the default on the @{" style button " Link "Style cycle button" } gadget.
@EndNode


@Node "PUBSCREEN"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} PUBSCREEN

   Syntax:  PUBSCREEN=<name>
   Default: Default public screen.

   If you want Luffar to open on an other public screen.
@EndNode


@Node "INTERLACE_SCALE"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} INTERLACE_SCALE

   Syntax:  INTERLACE_SCALE=TRUE | FALSE
   Default: Depending on resulotion.

   If you are using a hires/interlaced screen Luffar will scale
   in order to become square.
   If you don't like it you can override it with the INTERLACE_SCALE
   tooltype.
   If the Luffar window gets bigger than the current screen it will
   tell you and start with INTERLACE_SCALE disabled.

@EndNode


@Node "LEFTEDGE"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} LEFTEDGE

   Syntax:  LEFTEDGE= <number>
   Default: LEFTEDGE=50

   Set this to the number of pixels from the left edge of the
   screen to the Luffar window that you want when Luffar open
   its window. If the <number> is too big, Luffar will adjust
   to fit.

@EndNode


@Node "TOPEDGE"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} TOPEDGE

   Syntax:  TOPEDGE= <number>
   Default: TOPEDGE=10

   Set this to the number of pixels from the top of the screen
   to the Luffar window that you want when Luffar open its window.
   If the <number> is too big, Luffar will adjust so it fits.

@EndNode


@Node "ZIP_WINDOW"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} ZIP_WINDOW

   Syntax:  ZIP_WINDOW=TRUE | FALSE
   Default: ZIP_WINDOW=FALSE

   The zip (zoom) gadget in the upper right corner of the
   @{" Luffar window " Link "Luffar Window" } will toggle the size of the window
   between full size and bar size (small).
   If you enable ZIP_WINDOW Luffar will zip to small size when
   started.

@EndNode


@Node "SMALLEFTEDGE"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} SMALLEFTEDGE

   Syntax:  SMALLEFTEDGE= <number>
   Default: SMALLEFTEDGE=50

   Set this to the number of pixels from the left edge of the
   screen to the @{" zipped " Link "ZIP_WINDOW" } Luffar window
   that you want.
   If the <number> is too big, Luffar will adjust to fit.

@EndNode


@Node "SMALLTOPEDGE"

 @{fg highlight}o@{fg text} SMALLTOPEDGE

   Syntax:  SMALLTOPEDGE= <number>
   Default: SMALLTOPEDGE=10

   Set this to the number of pixels from the top of the screen
   to the @{" zipped " Link "ZIP_WINDOW" } Luffar window that
   you want.
   If the <number> is too big, Luffar will adjust so it fits.

@EndNode



